review_blob:
This pours a very deep brown color. It flows like it's very thick; almost reminds me of a thin strap molasses. Very good taste. It seems like the time in the barrel took a lot of the bitter notes out and replaced it with a hint of smokiness. Very good and enjoyable, and I'm not even a porter fan!

---Rated via Beer Buddy for iPhone

This one has a nose of an IPA. However, it has the taste of a smooth rich lager. Best of both worlds! Nice medium amber color. I just found another favorite beer!!!!

---Rated via Beer Buddy for iPhone

This one definitely has the nose of an IPA. Pours a nice dark amber color. You can definitely taste the grapes in this one, but overall it tastes watered down to me.

---Rated via Beer Buddy for iPhone

The aroma on this one is a little flat. Nice light to medium golden color. I really don't detect the pear aspect of this on at all. Overall ok beer. Different, but just ok.

---Rated via Beer Buddy for iPhone

This pours a more than average amber. Normal head. A bit bitter for my taste leaves me losing some points on the ratings.

---Rated via Beer Buddy for iPhone

This one pours a dark amber color with very little carbonation. Nice malt taste with no bitter hops. Very nice.

---Rated via Beer Buddy for iPhone

This is highly carbonated. My glass was half head for quite a while! Nice semi-cloudy amber color. Very nice taste. Will buy again, although the cork is a PITA.

---Rated via Beer Buddy for iPhone

This is all right, but the hops used are just a bit too bitter for my liking.

---Rated via Beer Buddy for iPhone

Deep amber red. Very piney hops. A little too bitter for my taste, but I'm not a hop head.

---Rated via Beer Buddy for iPhone

This one has hardly any noticeable nose. No hops presence, just a slight spice note. Color is a nice light amber. Taste is a pleasant slight spice. 

---Rated via Beer Buddy for iPhone

Looks like a normal porter, till you lift the glass. Nose is peanuts. Starts with a chocolate porter, ends with peanuts. Very interesting brew. If I'd be a porter buff, I'd be a fan.

---Rated via Beer Buddy for iPhone

A lightly hopped brew that is a nice medium dark amber color. A really good session beer.

---Rated via Beer Buddy for iPhone

This is one I hope they bring out of the scratch series and actually bottle!

---Rated via Beer Buddy for iPhone

Not much carbonation at all, almost tastes flat to me. A very nice golden color. Just an aftertaste of blueberries.

---Rated via Beer Buddy for iPhone

Typical adjunct beer. Has a very good flavor. Nice on a hot summer's day.

---Rated via Beer Buddy for iPhone
Strong and spicy.  Has very little carbonation at all, but the spiciness more than makes up for it.  Smacks of cinnamon.
beer_name: Tregs The Mad Elf Holiday Ale

review_blob: Currently my favorite beer.  Very complexe and interesting.  Starts with a strong grape flavor and crescendos with a very "spicy" flavor.  It finally ends on a soft grape note.
beer_name: Dogfish Head Midas Touch Golden Elixir
